help_commands.quickstart:
#  Quickstart
To start using Tauleph, first, set the channels in which you want it to respond in. Use `/channel_allow` in the channel you want it to speak in and `/channel_disallow` to disallow Tauleph from speaking there. To invoke Tauleph, simply type Tauleph's name along with your message. For example: 'Tauleph, what is the current time in Utah?' You can also reply to Tauleph's messages and it will respond without having to spell its name out.

For more commands or functionality, see `/help commands` or `/help functionality`.
help_commands.commands:
#  Commands
##  `/select_model:`
This command is used to switch the LLM's model. Currently, there are 15 available models, all which are useful for different purposes.
##  `/change_system_message:`
This command allows you to change the LLM's system message, AKA, its instructions. For example, you can set the system message to 'You are an angsty teen.' and the LLM will try its best to mimic an angsty teen. As of now, if you don't include Tauleph's server nickname in the system message, 'Your name is [insert nickname here]' will be added at the end of it. This feature is case sensitive.
##  `/current_system_message:`
This command will send a message containing the current system message.
##  `/channel_allow:`
This command adds the current channel to the list of channels in which Tauleph can respond.
##  `/channel_disallow:`
 This command removes the current channel from the list of channels in which Tauleph can respond.
##  `/help functionality:`
See what other functionality Tauleph has.
help_commands.functionality:
#  Functionality
##  Regeneration:
To regenerate Tauleph's messages, you can click to one of the following buttons. The repeat button (🔁) makes a new regeneration, while the arrow buttons (⬅➡️) allow you to navigate between previous regenerations.
##  Invoking:
To invoke Tauleph, you can do one of two things: type its name in your message or reply to one of Tauleph's messages. Example: 'Tauleph, what is Eggs Benedict?' You don't have to include Tauleph's name in your message if you reply to one of its messages.
##  Changing Tauleph's name:
You can customize the name it responds to by simply changing Tauleph's server nickname to your liking.
##  Audio and images:
Tauleph can see and hear any images or audio you send it. Just invoke it like you normally would, and it will reply accordingly. You can also speak to it using voice messages by first replying to one of its messages and then sending the voice message. It currently does not support gifs or videos of any kind.
##  Web search:
Tauleph can autonomously search the internet using a search engine. This extends its knowledge and usefulness. An example of how useful this is to query it about a recent event, and you'll see it respond with accurate, up-to-date information.
